## Root Skill View

The `RootSkillViewController` is the entry point for your `Skill`. When someone navigates to your `Skill`, the `RootSkillViewController` is the first `SkillView` that renders. Every `Skill` must have exactly one `RootSkillViewController`.

### Creating a Root Skill View

```bash
spruce create.view
```

The CLI will walk you through the following prompts:

1. **"Which are you creating?"** — Select "Skill View Controller".
2. **"Make this the Root View Controller?"** — Select Yes.

> **Note**: When creating a root, the name is automatically set to "Root" for you. The generated file will be placed at `src/skillViewControllers/Root.svc.ts`.

### How It's Identified

A `RootSkillViewController` is identified by setting `public static id = 'root'` on the class. When someone navigates to `https://{skillNamespace}.spruce.bot`, the `Heartwood Skill` looks up the `SkillViewController` registered with the id `root` for that `Skill` and renders it.

```ts
import {
    AbstractSkillViewController,
    SkillView,
} from '@sprucelabs/heartwood-view-controllers'

export default class RootSkillViewController extends AbstractSkillViewController {
    public static id = 'root'

    public render(): SkillView {
        return {
            layouts: [],
        }
    }
}
```

### Requiring Login

Override `getIsLoginRequired()` to require authentication before your `SkillView` loads. If it returns `true`, a `LoginCardViewController` will be rendered as a `Dialog`. If the person fails to login, they are redirected away.

<details>
<summary><strong>Test 1</strong>: Assert login is required</summary>

```ts
import { AbstractSpruceFixtureTest } from '@sprucelabs/spruce-test-fixtures'
import { vcAssert } from '@sprucelabs/heartwood-view-controllers'

export default class RootSkillViewTest extends AbstractSpruceFixtureTest {
    private vc!: RootSkillViewController

    protected async beforeEach() {
        await super.beforeEach()
        this.vc = this.views.Controller('eightbitstories.root', {})
    }

    @test()
    protected async requiresLogin() {
        // Step 1. Assert that getIsLoginRequired() returns true
        await vcAssert.assertLoginIsRequired(this.vc)
    }
}
```

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>Production 1</strong>: Require login</summary>

```ts
import {
    AbstractSkillViewController,
    SkillView,
} from '@sprucelabs/heartwood-view-controllers'

export default class RootSkillViewController extends AbstractSkillViewController {
    public static id = 'root'

    // Step 1. Override getIsLoginRequired to return true
    public async getIsLoginRequired() {
        return true
    }

    public render(): SkillView {
        return {
            layouts: [],
        }
    }
}
```

</details>

### Configuring Scope

Override `getScope()` to require an `Organization` or `Location` to be selected before your `SkillView` loads. This is how you tell `Heartwood` that your `SkillView`'s actions are scoped to a specific `Organization` or `Location`. Learn more in the [Scope Section](/concepts/scope/).

The available `ScopeFlags` are:

| Flag | Description |
|---|---|
| `'none'` | No scope required. |
| `'organization'` | Requires an `Organization` to be selected. |
| `'location'` | Requires a `Location` to be selected (implies `Organization`). |
| `'employed'` | Requires the person to be employed at the selected `Organization`. |

<details>
<summary><strong>Test 1</strong>: Assert scope is required</summary>

```ts
